features.name: Pirin Belongs to the pirin family
Glyco_hydro_63 involved in the assembly of lipopolysaccharide (LPS) at the surface of the outer membrane
MMPL Drug exporters of the RND superfamily
DapB_C,DapB_N Catalyzes the conversion of 4-hydroxy- tetrahydrodipicolinate (HTPA) to tetrahydrodipicolinate

Thymidylat_synt Catalyzes the reductive methylation of 2'-deoxyuridine- 5'-monophosphate (dUMP) to 2'-deoxythymidine-5'-monophosphate (dTMP) while utilizing 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate (mTHF) as the methyl donor and reductant in the reaction, yielding dihydrofolate (DHF) as a by-product. This enzymatic reaction provides an intracellular de novo source of dTMP, an essential precursor for DNA biosynthesis
DHFR_1 Key enzyme in folate metabolism. Catalyzes an essential reaction for de novo glycine and purine synthesis, and for DNA precursor synthesis
DHDPS Catalyzes the condensation of (S)-aspartate-beta- semialdehyde (S)-ASA and pyruvate to 4-hydroxy- tetrahydrodipicolinate (HTPA)
Lactamase_B,Lactamase_B_2,RMMBL An RNase that has 5'-3' exonuclease and possibly endonuclease activity. Involved in maturation of rRNA and in some organisms also mRNA maturation and or decay
FtsK_4TM,FtsK_SpoIIIE,Ftsk_gamma Belongs to the FtsK SpoIIIE SftA family
MTS Belongs to the protein N5-glutamine methyltransferase family
CDP-OH_P_transf Belongs to the CDP-alcohol phosphatidyltransferase class-I family
CinA Belongs to the CinA family
Arabino_trans_C,Arabinose_trans Cell wall arabinan synthesis protein

RecA Can catalyze the hydrolysis of ATP in the presence of single-stranded DNA, the ATP-dependent uptake of single-stranded DNA by duplex DNA, and the ATP-dependent hybridization of homologous single-stranded DNAs. It interacts with LexA causing its activation and leading to its autocatalytic cleavage
Glyoxalase glyoxalase bleomycin resistance protein dioxygenase
BPD_transp_1 Binding-protein-dependent transport system inner membrane component
BPD_transp_1 Binding-protein-dependent transport system inner membrane component

Radical_SAM,TRAM,UPF0004 Catalyzes the methylthiolation of N6- (dimethylallyl)adenosine (i(6)A), leading to the formation of 2- methylthio-N6-(dimethylallyl)adenosine (ms(2)i(6)A) at position 37 in tRNAs that read codons beginning with uridine
IPPT Catalyzes the transfer of a dimethylallyl group onto the adenine at position 37 in tRNAs that read codons beginning with uridine, leading to the formation of N6-(dimethylallyl)adenosine (i(6)A)
